1
00:00:18,252 --> 00:00:20,698
What am I supposed to do with this?

2
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:23,668
That's all I can spare right now.

3
00:00:23,724 --> 00:00:26,068
You want my kids living on Happy Meals?

4
00:00:28,262 --> 00:00:30,333
Sandi, I shouldn't even be here.

5
00:00:30,931 --> 00:00:33,343
Why are you being this way, Danny?

6
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:35,343
You know where you wanna be.

7
00:00:43,076 --> 00:00:47,388
Sammy's raving about this smoked
salmon he found in Nova Scotia.

8
00:00:47,447 --> 00:00:48,721
Lockport.

9
00:00:51,285 --> 00:00:52,457
Okay.

10
00:00:54,955 --> 00:00:56,730
You went there this morning.

11
00:00:57,524 --> 00:00:59,026
Mom, she has kids.

12
00:00:59,092 --> 00:01:00,730
They're not your kids.

13
00:01:02,362 --> 00:01:03,841
Kelly called.

14
00:01:04,932 --> 00:01:06,969
She needs to talk to you.

15
00:01:15,542 --> 00:01:17,419
Yeah, hi, honey. It's Daddy. Put Mommy on.

16
00:01:18,145 --> 00:01:19,419
It's Dad.

17
00:01:21,982 --> 00:01:23,427
You just got in?

18
00:01:23,483 --> 00:01:25,463
Yes. You know, the traffic. What's up?

19
00:01:25,519 --> 00:01:28,830
I won't be able to make it this afternoon.
My sister's coming in for the day.

20
00:01:29,957 --> 00:01:32,164
Oh, no, that's not acceptable.

21
00:01:32,793 --> 00:01:35,034
You have to call them and tell
them that we'll be there.

22
00:01:35,262 --> 00:01:37,037
We'll talk tonight.

23
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:45,477
Don't start with me, Mom, okay?

24
00:01:50,677 --> 00:01:52,179
Mike's coming in from Binghamton.

25
00:01:52,245 --> 00:01:54,521
All the cousins can be together.

26
00:01:54,581 --> 00:01:57,187
- What date is that?
- The fourth.

27
00:01:57,618 --> 00:02:00,224
I can't. It's the first day of Sukkoth.

28
00:02:01,221 --> 00:02:03,724
Sukkoth, the Festival of the Booths.

29
00:02:03,890 --> 00:02:05,961
And don't try to tell me
that sounds any weirder

30
00:02:06,026 --> 00:02:07,733
than the Feast of the Transfiguration.

31
00:02:07,794 --> 00:02:11,571
Mom hasn't seen your kids since,
what, just before Easter.

32
00:02:11,932 --> 00:02:13,377
I know.

33
00:02:13,634 --> 00:02:17,275
Maybe I'll just drive up one
Sunday with Jordie and Sharon.

34
00:02:19,539 --> 00:02:21,416
Is everything okay with you and Danny?

35
00:02:21,475 --> 00:02:23,512
You keep asking that. Yes.

36
00:02:23,877 --> 00:02:26,824
The business just takes up
a lot of his time.

37
00:02:27,481 --> 00:02:28,755
I have to run.

38
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:32,558
Housekeeper leaves at 4:00, and I don't want
the kids coming home to an empty house.

39
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:36,958
Tell Mom I'll call her tonight.

40
00:02:37,024 --> 00:02:38,196
Kelly,

41
00:02:39,459 --> 00:02:41,132
we can still talk.

42
00:04:25,398 --> 00:04:28,470
The lady who drove the kids home
from school found her about 5:30.

43
00:04:28,535 --> 00:04:29,878
Where was Mr. Sussman?

44
00:04:29,936 --> 00:04:32,041
Oh, he got home from work at 6:15.

45
00:04:32,105 --> 00:04:33,846
We were already here.

46
00:04:33,907 --> 00:04:35,386
He looked pretty shook-up.

47
00:04:35,442 --> 00:04:36,785
We'll see.

48
00:04:38,979 --> 00:04:42,426
See the hand spread across her neck?

49
00:04:42,482 --> 00:04:44,155
It's almost a foot wide.

50
00:04:44,985 --> 00:04:46,794
And this bruise here.

51
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:48,261
See? Knuckle marks.

52
00:04:48,321 --> 00:04:49,800
Smaller hand.

53
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:53,403
Yeah. A second assailant.
Came from that side.

54
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:54,962
She didn't stand a chance.

55
00:04:55,028 --> 00:04:56,735
Oh, but she fought back.

56
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:58,538
Her nails are torn.

57
00:05:04,404 --> 00:05:09,353
Threads from a gauze bandage?

58
00:05:11,478 --> 00:05:12,855
Now, that's

59
00:05:14,781 --> 00:05:16,419
antiseptic cream.

60
00:05:18,185 --> 00:05:21,189
One of them might have been
wearing a bandage.

61
00:05:22,856 --> 00:05:26,929
She came over the top of the hood

62
00:05:30,564 --> 00:05:32,441
to get away from them.

63
00:05:33,867 --> 00:05:36,074
But why did she go back in the car?

64
00:05:47,681 --> 00:05:49,092
The way out.

65
00:05:49,816 --> 00:05:51,261
Instead of overwhelming her

66
00:05:51,318 --> 00:05:52,729
as soon as she got out of the car,

67
00:05:52,786 --> 00:05:55,460
they hesitated.

68
00:05:55,555 --> 00:05:57,626
They gave her an opening.

69
00:05:58,925 --> 00:06:01,428
And then when they regained control,

70
00:06:02,128 --> 00:06:03,835
they used excessive force to kill her.

71
00:06:03,897 --> 00:06:05,205
Amateurs.

72
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:18,151
I thought that other detective I talked to,

73
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:19,383
he was running things.

74
00:06:19,446 --> 00:06:21,585
Your borough president called
the police commissioner.

75
00:06:21,648 --> 00:06:23,457
That's how the case came to us.

76
00:06:23,516 --> 00:06:25,928
Your family's prominent in the community.

77
00:06:25,986 --> 00:06:28,330
Well, my father was a very important man.

78
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:29,958
He helped a lot of people.

79
00:06:30,023 --> 00:06:32,902
Children, come in the kitchen with Grandma.

80
00:06:33,026 --> 00:06:34,232
Yeah, go ahead.

81
00:06:42,869 --> 00:06:46,840
It's a terrible thing they had
to find their mother that way.

82
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:53,921
Sussman Kosher Foods.

83
00:06:54,881 --> 00:06:57,088
I see your trucks around all the time.

84
00:06:57,817 --> 00:06:59,728
Everything good between
you and your employees?

85
00:06:59,786 --> 00:07:00,992
Yeah, we have no complaints.

86
00:07:01,054 --> 00:07:02,863
You and Mrs. Sussman?

87
00:07:04,658 --> 00:07:06,535
Anything we should know about?

88
00:07:08,228 --> 00:07:10,572
Everything was fine.

89
00:07:10,730 --> 00:07:13,176
The kids are doing well. We had our health.

90
00:07:16,069 --> 00:07:17,707
You have something in your eyes?

91
00:07:17,771 --> 00:07:19,273
No. Why?

92
00:07:21,408 --> 00:07:24,878
Blinking your eyes a lot, that usually
means you have something in your eyes.

93
00:07:24,945 --> 00:07:27,152
Or that your stress level has gone up.

94
00:07:27,213 --> 00:07:28,783
It's called the blink rate.

95
00:07:28,848 --> 00:07:31,351
Well, of course, I'm under a lot of stress.

96
00:07:31,418 --> 00:07:32,863
Of course.

97
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:41,371
Do you know where your wife
was earlier this afternoon?

98
00:07:41,428 --> 00:07:44,875
Her sister Anna had come down
from Albany for the day.

99
00:07:44,965 --> 00:07:46,740
Kelly was meeting her in the city.

100
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,871
Would she have been wearing any jewelry?

101
00:07:50,670 --> 00:07:53,116
She always had her wedding ring

102
00:07:53,173 --> 00:07:54,777
and a necklace

103
00:07:54,841 --> 00:07:57,822
that I bought her for our 10th anniversary.

104
00:07:58,578 --> 00:08:03,049
It had three diamonds,
for me and each of the kids.

105
00:08:09,289 --> 00:08:11,929
She always told me everything was fine.

106
00:08:12,225 --> 00:08:14,637
She was very private about her marriage.

107
00:08:15,228 --> 00:08:16,832
But something made you ask.

108
00:08:16,896 --> 00:08:20,105
Our mother had a stroke a few months ago.

109
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:22,271
I was calling Kelly late at night

110
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:23,905
with progress reports.

111
00:08:24,204 --> 00:08:26,582
A lot of times, Danny wasn't there.

112
00:08:26,639 --> 00:08:28,209
Where did she say he was?

113
00:08:28,975 --> 00:08:30,852
At some religious observance.

114
00:08:30,910 --> 00:08:33,083
You know, prayers.

115
00:08:34,214 --> 00:08:38,390
What religious observance takes place
late at night outside the home?

116
00:08:38,451 --> 00:08:40,556
I wouldn't know. I'm not Jewish.

117
00:08:41,488 --> 00:08:43,490
Oh, Kelly converted.

118
00:08:43,556 --> 00:08:44,830
Yes.

119
00:08:45,392 --> 00:08:48,999
So her children could be raised
in their father's faith.

120
00:08:53,099 --> 00:08:56,103
Kelly was familiar
with the Jewish traditions?

121
00:08:56,503 --> 00:08:58,073
She had to be.

122
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:00,783
The Sussmans are a very religious family.

123
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:04,852
Could you write down the dates and the times

124
00:09:04,911 --> 00:09:07,187
that you called her at home?

125
00:09:08,848 --> 00:09:11,260
There are three daily prayers
in the Jewish tradition

126
00:09:11,317 --> 00:09:13,695
and a man might leave the home
to go pray with the minion,

127
00:09:13,753 --> 00:09:15,130
with nine other men.

128
00:09:15,789 --> 00:09:18,030
Sussman might have had a
legitimate reason to be out.

129
00:09:18,091 --> 00:09:20,093
Except that the last prayer takes place

130
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:21,195
in the early evening.

131
00:09:21,261 --> 00:09:22,569
Which Mrs. Sussman would have known,

132
00:09:22,629 --> 00:09:24,836
being familiar with the traditions.

133
00:09:24,898 --> 00:09:26,309
She was covering for her husband.

134
00:09:26,366 --> 00:09:27,743
Seems to be part of her MO.

135
00:09:27,801 --> 00:09:30,247
She didn't let on that there were problems.

136
00:09:30,303 --> 00:09:31,839
She was better at it than he was.

137
00:09:31,905 --> 00:09:34,442
Two months ago, Tuesday night, 11:10 p.m.,

138
00:09:34,507 --> 00:09:36,851
he made a withdrawal for a
thousand bucks from an ATM

139
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:39,220
on the 600 block of Cuthpert Boulevard.

140
00:09:39,279 --> 00:09:40,622
What's the date on that?

141
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:44,184
There was a call to a business on Cuthpert.

142
00:09:45,819 --> 00:09:48,629
Here. Same day, from his cell phone,

143
00:09:48,688 --> 00:09:52,226
at 5:00 p.m. to Stan's Show Supplies.

144
00:09:52,659 --> 00:09:54,798
One block down from the ATM.

145
00:09:58,731 --> 00:10:00,802
Sussman, one of his checks bounced.

146
00:10:00,867 --> 00:10:03,473
We were holding his order until
he came up with one grand cash.

147
00:10:03,536 --> 00:10:04,776
What was in his order?

148
00:10:04,838 --> 00:10:06,408
I don't remember. Show stuff.

149
00:10:06,473 --> 00:10:09,682
You mean, like in Stan's Show stuff?
Maybe we should ask Stan.

150
00:10:09,742 --> 00:10:11,619
There is no Stan. There's Mr. Harland,

151
00:10:11,678 --> 00:10:13,487
and he's gonna be back here in an hour,

152
00:10:13,546 --> 00:10:15,116
and I gotta get these orders out.

153
00:10:15,181 --> 00:10:18,890
We'll write you a note, how you were
helping with a murder investigation.

154
00:10:24,524 --> 00:10:26,333
Now, Sussman's in the food business.

155
00:10:26,392 --> 00:10:28,372
What does he need lighting equipment for?

156
00:10:28,428 --> 00:10:31,034
Sussman told me he did charity events.

157
00:10:31,097 --> 00:10:35,011
Rented to Firefly Enterprises for
delivery on 10th Avenue in Manhattan.

158
00:10:35,068 --> 00:10:38,049
Spotlights, glitter ball, smoke machine.

159
00:10:38,938 --> 00:10:40,679
What's this abbreviation for?

160
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:44,711
A bubble bath setup.
It's a clear Lucite bathtub.

161
00:10:45,445 --> 00:10:46,446
Charity events.

162
00:10:46,513 --> 00:10:49,357
Charity must be the girl
who takes the bubble baths.

163
00:10:57,423 --> 00:11:00,370
Hey, how long I gotta wait in the car?

164
00:11:01,127 --> 00:11:03,733
Huh? Don't we gotta do a thing tonight?

165
00:11:05,198 --> 00:11:07,508
Next time will be on the house, baby.

166
00:11:11,437 --> 00:11:12,814
It's gonna take at least an hour

167
00:11:12,872 --> 00:11:14,613
to get all the way up there.

168
00:11:19,913 --> 00:11:22,325
Since when did you grow
a brain, huh? Come on.

169
00:11:25,118 --> 00:11:27,223
Sussman's got the lease
till the end of the year.

170
00:11:27,287 --> 00:11:28,960
After that, it's available.

171
00:11:29,022 --> 00:11:30,933
- Why'd he close up?
- I don't know.

172
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:32,367
Business was good.

173
00:11:32,425 --> 00:11:34,405
Is there a problem with the lights?

174
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:36,406
Fuse box blew three weeks ago.

175
00:11:36,462 --> 00:11:37,497
Just like that?

176
00:11:37,564 --> 00:11:40,738
Well, two days later I got a
letter from Sussman's lawyer

177
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:44,043
wanting to break the lease on
account of the electrical problem.

178
00:11:44,204 --> 00:11:47,151
- Do you mind if we have a look?
- No, go ahead.

179
00:11:49,742 --> 00:11:53,121
They poured acid behind the connector.

180
00:12:30,783 --> 00:12:32,262
That's blood.

181
00:12:37,557 --> 00:12:41,437
Well, he splashed acid on his arm.

182
00:12:41,494 --> 00:12:43,633
He would've had to reach in.

183
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:49,208
He came over here to wash it off,

184
00:12:51,070 --> 00:12:52,606
and he used this to wipe his wound.

185
00:12:52,672 --> 00:12:54,743
Gauze fibers on Kelly Sussman.

186
00:12:54,807 --> 00:12:57,515
Yeah, from the bandages of the killer.

187
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:01,425
He used this to cover his burn.

188
00:13:01,481 --> 00:13:04,394
Murderer, arsonist, jack of all trades.

189
00:13:04,917 --> 00:13:07,158
Yeah, master of none.

190
00:13:10,923 --> 00:13:13,836
The Arson Squad confirmed
they found traces of acid.

191
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:16,907
So this works for you? Sussman
risking jail time for arson

192
00:13:16,963 --> 00:13:18,237
just to skip out on a lease?

193
00:13:18,298 --> 00:13:20,300
- Money's money.
- Small money.

194
00:13:20,366 --> 00:13:23,643
- And what's this guy doing
running a strip joint?
- You have to ask?

195
00:13:23,703 --> 00:13:24,807
He wasn't running it alone.

196
00:13:24,871 --> 00:13:26,976
He filed a change of ownership 2 months ago.

197
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:29,077
He used to have a partner.

198
00:13:29,342 --> 00:13:30,616
Oh.

199
00:13:30,977 --> 00:13:33,184
And she spells it with an “i”.

200
00:13:34,113 --> 00:13:37,253
That's right. Sandi. Sandi Tortomassi.

201
00:13:37,317 --> 00:13:39,228
But I'm not a partner in the club anymore.

202
00:13:39,285 --> 00:13:40,992
I sold my share two months ago.

203
00:13:41,054 --> 00:13:42,533
Problems with your partners?

204
00:13:42,588 --> 00:13:44,864
No. Why would you think that?

205
00:13:44,924 --> 00:13:47,700
Well, we just heard that the
place was packed every night.

206
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:50,639
The only reason you would sell is if
you had a beef with your partners.

207
00:13:50,697 --> 00:13:54,235
Not to mention there was an attempted
arson there a few weeks ago.

208
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:58,043
By the way, is that something
burning? You're baking cookies.

209
00:13:59,005 --> 00:14:01,042
- Peanut butter.
- For my kids.

210
00:14:01,274 --> 00:14:03,914
And for the record, I didn't
have any beef with my partners.

211
00:14:03,976 --> 00:14:05,455
I wanted to pursue other interests.

212
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:07,218
Like baking cookies?

213
00:14:08,448 --> 00:14:11,759
Your other partners, that's Daniel Sussman?

214
00:14:11,818 --> 00:14:14,458
- Yes. His company.
- Firefly Enterprises.

215
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:17,296
The same people who own this house.

216
00:14:17,357 --> 00:14:19,963
We happened to notice Firefly put
up the money for this place.

217
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:22,597
That was a loan, against the
return on share of the club.

218
00:14:22,662 --> 00:14:24,369
A loan against your return?

219
00:14:26,899 --> 00:14:29,607
By the way, is there a Mr. Tortomassi?

220
00:14:29,669 --> 00:14:32,582
He's a drunk, passed out
in a trailer park in Ohio.

221
00:14:32,638 --> 00:14:36,211
Ohio? Didn't Firefly buy a condo in Dayton?

222
00:14:36,275 --> 00:14:38,551
- That was for my mother.
- Another loan.

223
00:14:38,611 --> 00:14:41,182
You are shouldering a lot of debt.

224
00:14:41,247 --> 00:14:43,557
My share of the club went
to pay off the other loans.

225
00:14:43,616 --> 00:14:45,562
That was the arrangement when I cashed out.

226
00:14:45,618 --> 00:14:48,155
So, let's see, he put up the money...

227
00:14:49,455 --> 00:14:51,594
What was your contribution again?

228
00:14:52,225 --> 00:14:54,569
I chose the decor, the ambiance.

229
00:14:55,328 --> 00:14:57,069
I supervised the employees.

230
00:14:57,130 --> 00:14:58,939
Waitresses, bouncers,

231
00:15:00,099 --> 00:15:01,339
strippers.

232
00:15:02,368 --> 00:15:06,077
And that's where you have
a lot of experience, right?

233
00:15:07,673 --> 00:15:09,243
Oh, it's the outfit.

234
00:15:09,308 --> 00:15:11,379
Not exactly the standard issue

235
00:15:11,444 --> 00:15:13,014
Westchester soccer mom.

236
00:15:14,313 --> 00:15:16,919
You're very toned and

237
00:15:18,084 --> 00:15:19,256
flexible.

238
00:15:19,318 --> 00:15:21,855
Sussman catch your act at a
strip club? Is that how you met?

239
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:23,798
You know, if you're trying to humiliate me,

240
00:15:23,856 --> 00:15:25,392
I've heard it all before.

241
00:15:25,792 --> 00:15:29,604
I want you to leave now, before
my kids get up from their nap.

242
00:15:31,831 --> 00:15:33,902
How did you find out where
Sandi used to work?

243
00:15:33,966 --> 00:15:36,378
She never told strangers
what she did for a living.

244
00:15:36,436 --> 00:15:38,882
Even strippers have to file W-2s.

245
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:41,384
Your manager said you used
to share a place with her.

246
00:15:41,441 --> 00:15:43,478
Yeah, before she got the house.

247
00:15:43,543 --> 00:15:47,047
She had some help with that,
from this man, Daniel Sussman?

248
00:15:47,447 --> 00:15:49,358
Yeah, sure, Danny.

249
00:15:49,415 --> 00:15:51,088
He met Sandi here?

250
00:15:52,618 --> 00:15:55,565
Danny'd come in, throw around a lot of money.

251
00:15:56,289 --> 00:15:58,166
He really liked Sandi.

252
00:15:58,424 --> 00:16:00,404
He told her he wanted to give her the world.

253
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:02,337
And she probably thought he could afford it.

254
00:16:02,395 --> 00:16:04,807
Sandi liked him because he was a gentleman.

255
00:16:04,864 --> 00:16:06,673
Bought her a house, set her up in a business.

256
00:16:06,732 --> 00:16:08,040
That was all his idea.

257
