00:30:13,478 --> 00:30:16,925
Wouldn't be smart of them to alienate voters.

517
00:30:16,982 --> 00:30:18,984
No, it wouldn't be smart.

518
00:30:19,117 --> 00:30:22,655
So we help to prepare a get,
a Jewish divorce decree.

519
00:30:22,721 --> 00:30:25,361
Then she had to present it to
her husband for him to sign.

520
00:30:25,424 --> 00:30:27,335
Sounds pretty straightforward.

521
00:30:28,060 --> 00:30:31,041
Except Kelly had to find
two witnesses to go with her.

522
00:30:31,096 --> 00:30:32,973
People active in her synagogue.

523
00:30:33,031 --> 00:30:34,374
She couldn't find anyone.

524
00:30:34,433 --> 00:30:36,208
No one wanted to be her witness.

525
00:30:36,668 --> 00:30:38,045
Even her rabbi wouldn't help.

526
00:30:38,103 --> 00:30:39,275
The Sussman family...

527
00:30:39,338 --> 00:30:41,409
They carry a lot of weight in the community.

528
00:30:41,473 --> 00:30:43,714
Danny Sussman didn't want a divorce.

529
00:30:43,775 --> 00:30:47,188
He wanted a reconciliation.
But Kelly had no choice.

530
00:30:47,879 --> 00:30:51,383
If she didn't have a get, she'd risk
losing her kids in a custody fight.

531
00:30:51,450 --> 00:30:54,761
When Kelly canceled the
mediation, did she reschedule?

532
00:30:54,820 --> 00:30:55,855
No.

533
00:30:56,655 --> 00:30:58,862
So the reconciliation was off?

534
00:31:01,626 --> 00:31:04,573
She told me she had a better way
of getting what she wanted.

535
00:31:05,831 --> 00:31:07,606
Custody of her kids.

536
00:31:08,934 --> 00:31:12,211
I told her, no matter what,
Danny'd make a problem.

537
00:31:14,239 --> 00:31:16,776
You know what, Danny's
never been the problem.

538
00:31:16,842 --> 00:31:20,051
I mean, he doesn't have
the clout or the backbone

539
00:31:20,112 --> 00:31:22,285
to bend the community to his will.

540
00:31:24,049 --> 00:31:25,824
But his mother does.

541
00:31:26,551 --> 00:31:28,792
She cleaned up his mess when he stole money,

542
00:31:28,854 --> 00:31:31,767
and now she's fighting to save his marriage.

543
00:31:34,559 --> 00:31:37,563
I can't find the invoice
for the Gellis account.

544
00:31:37,662 --> 00:31:39,198
Do you have it?

545
00:31:40,732 --> 00:31:42,973
- Danny?
- I can't help it, Mom.

546
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:46,341
She destroyed Kelly.
Now she's gonna destroy me.

547
00:31:46,405 --> 00:31:49,147
- Stop it, stop it.
- I deserve it. I brought her into our life.

548
00:31:49,207 --> 00:31:51,118
- Don't talk like that.
- I deserve what happens to me.

549
00:31:51,176 --> 00:31:53,520
You deserve what you let happen.

550
00:31:54,112 --> 00:31:57,491
We have friends, influence, respect.

551
00:31:57,549 --> 00:31:59,426
They don't respect me.

552
00:32:00,051 --> 00:32:02,895
They respect the name your father gave you.

553
00:32:03,622 --> 00:32:05,659
The name you gave your son.

554
00:32:06,558 --> 00:32:08,629
If you can't stand up for yourself,

555
00:32:08,693 --> 00:32:10,934
at least stand up for the name.

556
00:32:14,065 --> 00:32:16,102
I wish Dad was still here.

557
00:32:18,770 --> 00:32:20,374
It's better he's not.

558
00:32:30,148 --> 00:32:32,628
Kelly was working in one of the big hotels

559
00:32:32,684 --> 00:32:35,221
in New York City when she met Danny.

560
00:32:35,587 --> 00:32:37,931
She told me he was very sweet.

561
00:32:38,824 --> 00:32:40,269
A real gentleman.

562
00:32:41,827 --> 00:32:44,774
She didn't tell me he was a Jewish gentleman.

563
00:32:45,330 --> 00:32:47,071
And that bothered you?

564
00:32:47,132 --> 00:32:48,372
Well,

565
00:32:49,034 --> 00:32:53,505
I was wishing that Kelly would
meet a nice Catholic boy.

566
00:32:54,539 --> 00:32:57,486
Just like I'm sure Mrs. Sussman wished

567
00:32:57,542 --> 00:33:00,352
her son had met a nice Jewish girl.

568
00:33:00,479 --> 00:33:02,789
Is that the impression that she gave you?

569
00:33:02,848 --> 00:33:06,057
Oh, she didn't warm up to
Kelly till after the wedding.

570
00:33:07,686 --> 00:33:10,394
We never even got a hug from that woman.

571
00:33:12,123 --> 00:33:14,330
Your daughter was a devout Catholic?

572
00:33:14,459 --> 00:33:16,962
Well, she grew up in the church.

573
00:33:17,028 --> 00:33:18,905
She sang in the choir.

574
00:33:19,731 --> 00:33:22,234
She loved the Virgin Mary.

575
00:33:26,505 --> 00:33:30,317
Well, then, converting to Judaism

576
00:33:30,909 --> 00:33:33,480
must have been a big decision for her.

577
00:33:33,545 --> 00:33:35,821
Was that something that Danny
pressured her to do?

578
00:33:35,881 --> 00:33:37,258
Not Danny.

579
00:33:37,616 --> 00:33:39,357
He just wanted to be with Kelly.

580
00:33:39,417 --> 00:33:41,226
They even talked about eloping.

581
00:33:41,286 --> 00:33:42,765
Mrs. Sussman.

582
00:33:43,588 --> 00:33:45,397
She made a big stink.

583
00:33:45,991 --> 00:33:48,699
And Kelly was stubborn.

584
00:33:50,695 --> 00:33:53,539
But then Kelly gave in.

585
00:33:54,966 --> 00:33:56,468
All of a sudden.

586
00:33:57,736 --> 00:33:59,511
Did she explain why?

587
00:33:59,704 --> 00:34:00,739
No.

588
00:34:01,172 --> 00:34:03,516
Two weeks later they were married.

589
00:34:08,313 --> 00:34:11,317
No, sir, I'm not sure what
evidence they're developing

590
00:34:11,616 --> 00:34:13,118
I know, but...

591
00:34:13,885 --> 00:34:15,193
Yes, sir.

592
00:34:16,154 --> 00:34:18,225
The Brooklyn DA's moving on the girl.

593
00:34:18,290 --> 00:34:20,793
They're tangling with some
community pressure over there.

594
00:34:20,859 --> 00:34:22,770
A community known as Ursula Sussman.

595
00:34:22,827 --> 00:34:24,670
You still haven't sold me on that yet.

596
00:34:24,729 --> 00:34:26,106
And what's all this?

597
00:34:26,531 --> 00:34:28,807
Thirteen-year-old checks from her account.

598
00:34:28,867 --> 00:34:30,847
Am I gonna kick myself for asking?

599
00:34:32,971 --> 00:34:36,418
This one's for $75,000 made out to cash.

600
00:34:37,842 --> 00:34:40,288
Just before her son's wedding 13 years ago.

601
00:34:40,345 --> 00:34:43,121
Could've been for the dress,
for the reception hall.

602
00:34:43,181 --> 00:34:45,957
The second check is the same amount.

603
00:34:47,886 --> 00:34:51,993
$75,000 to cash three months later, in April.

604
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:57,338
And it's just a week after her...

605
00:34:57,929 --> 00:35:01,172
Her grandson was born.

606
00:35:05,103 --> 00:35:07,743
I need to see my friend, Max.

607
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:10,547
He's a rabbi.

608
00:35:11,610 --> 00:35:13,817
We need to get Danny and his mother in here.

609
00:35:18,316 --> 00:35:20,523
He knows we have this meeting?

610
00:35:20,585 --> 00:35:22,963
He's usually back from lunch by now.

611
00:35:23,021 --> 00:35:26,434
I'm sorry. There was a
long line at the bodega.

612
00:35:28,226 --> 00:35:32,333
Did Detective Eames explain that
we needed some things clarified?

613
00:35:32,397 --> 00:35:34,343
Yes. About my marriage.

614
00:35:34,399 --> 00:35:37,846
Yeah, right. You and your wife
were trying to make a fresh start.

615
00:35:37,902 --> 00:35:39,882
Yes. We were trying.

616
00:35:39,938 --> 00:35:41,383
Your idea or hers?

617
00:35:41,439 --> 00:35:44,852
Well, both. We both wanted
to go for counseling.

618
00:35:45,243 --> 00:35:48,190
Sussman pickles. I've always been a big fan.

619
00:35:48,446 --> 00:35:51,620
You made appointments
at the Nashot Chayl Center?

620
00:35:51,816 --> 00:35:54,194
Yes. Kelly arranged it.

621
00:35:54,452 --> 00:35:57,092
The people there told us
when she first contacted them,

622
00:35:57,155 --> 00:35:59,658
Kelly was dead set on a divorce.

623
00:35:59,724 --> 00:36:02,227
Oh, that's between a husband and a wife.

624
00:36:02,293 --> 00:36:06,435
These people shouldn't be blabbering
about confidential information.

625
00:36:07,298 --> 00:36:10,802
Well, I guess it really
doesn't matter now, does it?

626
00:36:13,238 --> 00:36:14,649
I guess not.

627
00:36:16,408 --> 00:36:20,379
You felt... Well, you still feel guilty.

628
00:36:21,913 --> 00:36:24,325
I mean, you would have given
her anything she wanted

629
00:36:24,382 --> 00:36:25,918
in the divorce.

630
00:36:26,117 --> 00:36:28,028
Even custody of the kids?

631
00:36:28,086 --> 00:36:32,262
She was a good mother and fighting
over custody would have hurt them.

632
00:36:33,224 --> 00:36:35,465
What if Kelly went back
to the Catholic church?

633
00:36:35,527 --> 00:36:37,165
Under Jewish law,

634
00:36:37,429 --> 00:36:40,740
the kids wouldn't have been considered
Jewish anymore, would they?

635
00:36:40,799 --> 00:36:42,107
She wouldn't have done that.

636
00:36:42,167 --> 00:36:43,942
What, someone who'd been hurt?

637
00:36:44,869 --> 00:36:47,873
Who was angry, divorced, alone?

638
00:36:47,939 --> 00:36:49,509
Who knows what she'd do?

639
00:36:52,744 --> 00:36:57,420
Well, thank heaven there was someone
in the family still thinking straight.

640
00:36:58,116 --> 00:36:59,925
Right, Mrs. Sussman?

641
00:37:01,286 --> 00:37:02,959
I mean, if it wasn't for you,

642
00:37:03,021 --> 00:37:05,592
Kelly might've run off
with your grandchildren

643
00:37:05,657 --> 00:37:07,967
and turned them into who knows what.

644
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:12,503
Kelly just needed some time
to get over her anger.

645
00:37:15,934 --> 00:37:17,845
Well, she got over it, all right.

646
00:37:18,436 --> 00:37:20,814
Do you wanna know what she
told them at the center?

647
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:23,114
She told them that

648
00:37:23,174 --> 00:37:25,814
she had a way of getting what she wanted.

649
00:37:25,877 --> 00:37:28,790
Not from you, but from your mother.

650
00:37:29,581 --> 00:37:31,527
What do you suppose she meant by that?

651
00:37:31,583 --> 00:37:34,029
We don't know. We're not mind readers.

652
00:37:34,385 --> 00:37:35,887
Neither are we.

653
00:37:36,421 --> 00:37:39,925
But we're pretty good at connecting the dots.

654
00:37:39,991 --> 00:37:43,336
First dot, Big Louie Bernoff.

655
00:37:44,028 --> 00:37:46,508
You might know him as a murder suspect.

656
00:37:46,765 --> 00:37:49,644
But six years ago, he was
also the owner of a van

657
00:37:49,701 --> 00:37:52,614
he bought used from his
father, the mechanic.

658
00:37:53,705 --> 00:37:55,685
That sound familiar?

659
00:37:56,875 --> 00:38:01,381
Because your dad helped Louie's father

660
00:38:01,446 --> 00:38:04,290
immigrate from the Soviet Union,

661
00:38:04,349 --> 00:38:07,922
I mean, just like he helped
hundreds of other refugees.

662
00:38:07,986 --> 00:38:11,957
You dad even gave him the contract to
service your company's delivery vans.

663
00:38:12,190 --> 00:38:13,965
So, that means nothing.

664
00:38:14,025 --> 00:38:17,666
Your father helped hundreds
of people, thousands.

665
00:38:17,996 --> 00:38:20,977
This is... It's just a... Just a...

666
00:38:22,167 --> 00:38:23,305
Fluke?

667
00:38:25,236 --> 00:38:28,547
It could be a fluke if Sandi Tortomassi

668
00:38:28,973 --> 00:38:31,180
hired him to kill Kelly.

669
00:38:32,844 --> 00:38:34,346
But she didn't.

670
00:38:38,216 --> 00:38:40,560
Your wife wasn't a threat to her.

671
00:38:42,787 --> 00:38:44,232
Your wife was a threat to your mother.

672
00:38:44,289 --> 00:38:46,667
Oh, that's just ridiculous.

673
00:38:48,059 --> 00:38:49,766
Kelly had something on her.

674
00:38:51,429 --> 00:38:54,171
Something so shameful

675
00:38:56,034 --> 00:38:59,880
that Kelly thought your mother
might give up her grand-kids

676
00:38:59,938 --> 00:39:01,144
to keep it quiet.

677
00:39:01,206 --> 00:39:02,685
That's not true.

678
00:39:02,740 --> 00:39:05,186
I have nothing to be ashamed of.

679
00:39:07,212 --> 00:39:08,589
Second dot.

680
00:39:12,450 --> 00:39:17,092
Your pregnant Catholic fiancée.

681
00:39:18,990 --> 00:39:23,302
Three words that made
your mother very unhappy.

682
00:39:23,494 --> 00:39:24,495
That's okay.

683
00:39:24,562 --> 00:39:26,803
Kelly's mother wasn't too
thrilled about it either.

684
00:39:26,865 --> 00:39:29,243
Especially when she
converted out of the blue.

685
00:39:31,336 --> 00:39:34,249
Or should I say out of the green?

686
00:39:35,840 --> 00:39:37,717
That summer after you were married,

687
00:39:37,775 --> 00:39:40,847
Kelly bought her mother
a house for a $150,000?

688
00:39:41,412 --> 00:39:45,952
Yes, that was a settlement that she'd
gotten for an old car accident.

689
00:39:48,419 --> 00:39:49,762
Third dot.

690
00:39:51,489 --> 00:39:54,663
Two $75,000 checks

691
00:39:55,360 --> 00:39:58,500
drawn from your mother's
account 13 years ago.

692
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:04,842
Kelly bought the house with those checks.

693
00:40:07,572 --> 00:40:09,051
The first one

694
00:40:09,741 --> 00:40:13,780
is dated one week before Kelly converted.

695
00:40:14,646 --> 00:40:17,855
The second one is dated two
days after your son's Bris,

696
00:40:17,916 --> 00:40:22,092
after his circumcision that
welcomed him into the faith.

697
00:40:30,762 --> 00:40:32,537
If anyone found out,

698
00:40:33,197 --> 00:40:35,006
all the good will,

699
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:38,647
all the influence your father garnered

700
00:40:39,804 --> 00:40:43,081
from his good work and his religious devotion

701
00:40:44,075 --> 00:40:46,077
would have disappeared like

702
00:40:48,579 --> 00:40:50,320
smoke in the wind.

703
00:40:52,216 --> 00:40:55,823
Your family name would have been
disgraced, and the family business.

704
00:40:57,155 --> 00:40:59,465
Kelly was gonna tell everyone.

705
00:41:03,695 --> 00:41:08,508
Unless your mother let her
have custody of your kids.

706
00:41:08,566 --> 00:41:09,636
Mom,

707
00:41:10,935 --> 00:41:12,471
tell me you...

708
00:41:13,304 --> 00:41:16,342
She did. She hired Big Louie
to kill your wife

709
00:41:16,407 --> 00:41:19,945
and plant her necklace
in your girlfriend's garage.

710
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:23,850
I'll bet

711
00:41:23,915 --> 00:41:26,987
that your mother doesn't think
that she even did anything wrong.

712
00:41:29,153 --> 00:41:32,999
I'll bet that she thinks that she was just
cleaning up another one of your messes.

713
00:41:36,928 --> 00:41:39,966
Aren't you gonna get angry at her?
She killed your wife!

714
00:41:43,601 --> 00:41:45,444
Come on, Danny.

715
00:41:46,504 --> 00:41:48,609
When are you gonna grow up?

716
00:41:50,908 --> 00:41:55,152
When are you gonna
take your balls back from her?

717
00:42:00,918 --> 00:42:02,329
How could you, Mom?

718
00:42:04,489 --> 00:42:06,526
How in the hell could you?

719
00:42:08,826 --> 00:42:10,737
If you'd only listened.

720
00:42:13,765 --> 00:42:16,211
I told you she was no good for you.

721
00:42:18,002 --> 00:42:20,039
So I did what I had to do.

722
00:42:20,438 --> 00:42:24,284
For the family. Always for the family.

723
00:42:24,475 --> 00:42:27,479
What family? You killed the family!

724
00:42:29,947 --> 00:42:32,484
You're under arrest,
Mrs. Sussman, for murder.

725
00:42:32,550 --> 00:42:34,188
Please turn around.

726
00:42:39,791 --> 00:42:41,737
Danny, do something.

727
00:42:43,494 --> 00:42:44,734
Danny,

728
00:42:46,164 --> 00:42:47,666
do something!

729
00:43:02,613 --> 00:43:03,921
She broke the laws of her faith,

730
00:43:03,981 --> 00:43:05,892
so what does she do about it?

731
00:43:05,950 --> 00:43:07,691
You commit one sin,

732
00:43:08,052 --> 00:43:10,498
the next ones come a little easier.

